blog.name: julesfalkhunter
blog.title: fragments of broken dreams . . .
blog.description:
All the photographs posted here are original work from photographers I follow  on tumblr . My aim is  twofold, share the inspiration, and give photographers a bit more exposure .     
 I am also part of the  Lux Lit  team of rebloggers, and ms-excuse me with Thierry Facon, where the main focus is to bring you lesser known photographs that we feel deserve some more attention. 
 Please feel free to contact me if you have any questions or comments, or would  like me to check out your blog;  I'm on a constant quest for new photography blogs to follow .
julesfalkhunter@gmail.com

title: About my Blog...
body:
I’m usually not the person to rant or care that much about changes, but this time I can’t ignore the changes Tumblr came up with. I do not post any hardcore stuff except for shirtless buffed men or women with cleavage (maximum I do), if you can call that hardcore at all. Some of my post were flagged as explicit when there’re literally just faces while some other pictures, I would understand, are not. This censorship is absolutely ridiculous.

So in the future I’ll mainly post somewhere else. Maybe Patreon or Twitter who knows. I’ve not yet made up my mind.

I will still keep using Tumblr, but will limit the things I post here.

Links to other social media platforms can be found in my blog.
